{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/18116", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/18116/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/18116/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/18116/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/18116", "id": 46087319, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0NjA4NzMxOQ==", "number": 18116, "title": "Incorrect lifetime inference?", "user": {"login": "canndrew", "id": 5555066, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjU1NTUwNjY=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5555066?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew", "html_url": "https://github.com/canndrew", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2014-10-17T10:58:40Z", "updated_at": "2014-10-19T03:27:32Z", "closed_at": "2014-10-19T03:27:32Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The following code fails to compile:\n\n```\n#![feature(unboxed_closures)]\n#![feature(overloaded_calls)]\n\nuse std::io::stdio::stdin;\n\nfn foo<'a, T>(f: &mut T)\n    where T: FnMut(&'a mut (Reader + 'static))\n{\n  let mut r = stdin();\n  (*f)(&mut r as &mut Reader);\n}\n\nfn main() {\n  let mut c = |&mut: bar: &mut Reader| ();\n  foo(&mut c);\n}\n```\n\nWith the error:\n\n```\n<anon>:10:13: 10:14 error: `r` does not live long enough\n<anon>:10   (*f)(&mut r as &mut Reader);\n                      ^\n<anon>:8:1: 11:2 note: reference must be valid for the lifetime 'a as defined on the block at 8:0...\n<anon>:8 {\n<anon>:9   let mut r = stdin();\n<anon>:10   (*f)(&mut r as &mut Reader);\n<anon>:11 }\n<anon>:8:1: 11:2 note: ...but borrowed value is only valid for the block at 8:0\n<anon>:8 {\n<anon>:9   let mut r = stdin();\n<anon>:10   (*f)(&mut r as &mut Reader);\n<anon>:11 }\nerror: aborting due to previous error\n```\n\nIf I understand correctly, when the lifetime of a function argument isn't specified then it's assumed to be the lifetime of the function call. Therefore `'a` should be instantiated as the lifetime of the call of `(*f)` on line 10, in which case `r` should outlive it.\n\nSo is this a bug in rust? Or is there another way to write this?\n", "closed_by": {"login": "canndrew", "id": 5555066, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjU1NTUwNjY=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5555066?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew", "html_url": "https://github.com/canndrew", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/canndrew/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/18116/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/18116/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed"}